CASH-FLOW HEDGES

FOR A DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENT DESIGNATED AS A CASH-FLOW HEDGE, THE EFFECTIVE PORTION OF THE DERIVATIVES GAIN

(LOSS) IS INITIALLY REPORTED AS A COMPONENT OF OTHER COMPREHENSIVE INCOME (OCI) AND IS SUBSEQUENTLY RECOGNIZED IN EARNINGS WHEN THE HEDGED EXPOSURE IS RECOGNIZED IN EARNINGS. FOR OPTIONS DESIGNATED AS CASH-FLOW HEDGES, CHANGES IN THE

TIME VALUE ARE EXCLUDED FROM THE ASSESSMENT OF HEDGE EFFECTIVENESS AND ARE RECOGNIZED IN EARNINGS. GAINS (LOSSES) ON DERIVATIVES REPRESENTING EITHER HEDGE COMPONENTS EXCLUDED FROM THE ASSESSMENT OF EFFECTIVENESS OR HEDGE INEFFECTIVENESS ARE

RECOGNIZED IN EARNINGS. DURING FISCAL YEAR 2009, WE RECOGNIZED THE FOLLOWING GAINS (LOSSES) RELATED TO FOREIGN EXCHANGE CONTRACTS.

